Subject: Sahara (House of Lords album) 
To: Shawn
Content:
Sahara is the second studio album by the American hard rock band House of Lords, released on August 21, 1990. The album was recorded without original guitarist Lanny Cordola, but with Michael Guy as the band's guitarist. Still, the album features many guest contributors on guitar, such as Doug Aldrich (Whitesnake, Hurricane), Rick Nielsen (Cheap Trick), Chris Impellitteri (Impellitteri) and Mandy Meyer (Asia, Krokus). Other contributors on the albums are White Lion's Mike Tramp, Cheap Trick's Robin Zander, Steeler's Ron Keel, Autograph's Steve Plunkett and Giuffria's David Glen Eisley, all on backing vocals. The album reached position No. 121 in the The Billboard 200 chart on February 23, 1991.[2]
